    "body": "For which component is this, I just did a quick test for hits and can't reproduce: \r\n\r\n```ts\r\ntest('renders empty template using `html`', async () => {\r\n  const container = document.createElement('div');\r\n  const searchClient = createMockedSearchClient();\r\n\r\n  const search = instantsearch({ indexName: 'indexName', searchClient });\r\n\r\n  search.addWidgets([\r\n    hits({\r\n      container,\r\n      templates: {\r\n        item(_, { html }) {\r\n          return html``;\r\n        },\r\n      },\r\n    }),\r\n  ]);\r\n\r\n  search.start();\r\n\r\n  await wait(0);\r\n\r\n  expect(container).toMatchInlineSnapshot(`\r\n    <div>\r\n      <div\r\n        class=\"ais-Hits\"\r\n      >\r\n        <ol\r\n          class=\"ais-Hits-list\"\r\n        >\r\n          <li\r\n            class=\"ais-Hits-item\"\r\n          />\r\n          <li\r\n            class=\"ais-Hits-item\"\r\n          />\r\n        </ol>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  `);\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf there's anything happening that's causing it, I think it may be around here in the code, where undefined somehow gets casted as a string? If there's a clear repro, I wonder if the `content === null` check should be just `!content` as that shouldn't render in any case.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/blob/a047839060bc7be5048a49a07af639ea67bb237c/packages/instantsearch.js/src/components/Template/Template.tsx#L101",
